<br>
I recently got a full respec on my skald after deciding to switch back to axe from hammer. The weapon type is not important (my choice was based upon my available equipment). Here is some data I collected in order to determine what the best spec would be. My final choice: 46 BS/47 Axe/5 Parry.<br>
<br>
Plague Caps:<br>
35+14 Weapon spec=545<br>
36+14 Weapon spec=549<br>
39+14 Weapon spec=562<br>
47+14 Weapon spec=597<br>
<br>
Weaponskills:<br>
35+14 Weapon spec=965<br>
36+14 Weapon spec=972<br>
39+14 Weapon spec=991<br>
47+14 Weapon spec=1043<br>
<br>
Parry results vs. 802 Weaponskill Healer, 17+14 parry (1600+ attacks each):<br>
103 Dexterity=17.7%<br>
185 Dexterity=20.2%<br>
<br>
DD results vs. 22% resist, all power relics:<br>
43 DD=184<br>
44 DD=189<br>
50 DD=212<br>
<br>
Apx. melee damage/swing swinging at 4.9 spd vs. 29+10% slash resist, 1419 WS, using plague with 3 melee relics:<br>
250<br>
<br>
<br>
Ok here are the assumptions I made:<br>
1. I will swing 3x for every time I do DD's.<br>
2. I will be buffed most of the time I play.<br>
3. Melee relic and power relic damage gain is irrelevant since the comparison is relative.<br>
4. Going from 46 to 50 Battlesong costs 4 Weapon spec.<br>
<br>
Cap damage gain per spec point=(597/545-1)/12=0.8%<br>
Weaponskill gain per spec point=(1043/965-1)/12=0.67%<br>
Overall melee damage gain per spec point=1.008*1.0067-1=1.47%<br>
Percentage gain from 4 Weapon spec=1.47%*4=5.9%<br>
Damage gain in 15 seconds from 4 Weapon spec=0.059*250*3=44<br>
Damage gain from lvl 50 shout vs. lvl 40 shout=23<br>
<br>
Thus I decided 50 BS was inferior to 46 BS.<br>
<br>
<br>
Overall melee damage gain per spec point=1.008*1.0067-1=1.47%<br>
Parry gain per point of parry=(20.2%-5%)/31=0.49%<br>
Points of parry to equal 1 point of Weapon spec=3<br>
<br>
Let us look at the various 46 BS templates with the first being the norm.<br>
<br>
44 Weapon/17 Parry<br>
45 Weapon/14 Parry (gains 1.47% melee damage, loses 1.47% parry)<br>
46 Weapon/10 Parry (gains 1.47% melee damage, loses 1.96% parry)<br>
47 Weapon/5 Parry (gains 1.47% melee damage, loses 2.45% parry)<br>
<br>
At this point I made three further assumptions that I think most will agree with:<br>
1. Any time you are in a position to parry, you will be doing melee damage but any time you are doing melee damage you are not necessarily in a position to parry.<br>
2. The chance to parry can be reduced in RvR due to multiple attackers.<br>
3. The percentage of your overall damage that comes from melee is approximately equal or less than the percentage of your overall damage taken that is parryable.<br>
<br>
I think given those two assumptions, that it's clear that 47 Weapon/5 Parry is the best 46 BS template as you are trading parry for melee damage at only a 5:3 ratio. I would say anything better than 2:1 (heck, maybe even 3:1) should be traded in for melee damage rather than parry. <p>Eka, lvl 50 skald Percival</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A> at: 10/12/03 12:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=roimma@teamskald>Roimma</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/11/03 11:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=733.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Drop parry, raise weapon spec</span><hr size=1> that's my spec <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
